SSyynnooppssiiss
       /u95/bin/suscfg -d
       /u95/bin/suscfg -e
       /u95/bin/suscfg -n

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  suscfg command performs the tasks necessary to enable
       and disable conformance with the X/Open UNIX95 Brand (Sin-
       gle UNIX Specification) on the running system.

       This  command  performs  the following tasks: reconfigures
       the UNIX system kernel, changing the value of the RSTCHOWN
       kernel  tunable  parameter changes the default login shell
       for new users edits /etc/profile

       For more detail, see

   CCoommmmaanndd ooppttiioonnss::
       Disables conformance and reconfigures the kernel; this may
       take  a few minutes.  Enables conformance and reconfigures
       the kernel; this may take a few minutes.  Queries the cur-
       rent running system and prints a message indicated whether
       or not UNIX95 conformance is  currently  enabled  or  dis-
       abled.

   NNoottiicceess
       Use  of  either the -d or -e options reconfigures the UNIX
       kernel; you must reboot the system to rebuild  the  kernel
       and install it as the running system.

